searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"ExBarcode","doc":"Pure Elixir barcode encoding library.\n\nSupports Code 128 (full ASCII). Returns bar patterns as lists of\nmodule widths suitable for any renderer (PDF, SVG, Canvas, etc.).","ref":"ExBarcode.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Standard encoding - ExBarcode","doc":"{:ok, bars} = ExBarcode.encode(\"Hello-123\")\n\nReturns alternating bar/space module widths.","ref":"ExBarcode.html#module-standard-encoding"},{"type":"module","title":"Shaped encoding (creative barcodes) - ExBarcode","doc":"{:ok, result} = ExBarcode.encode_shaped(\"DEMOCAMP\", shape: :rv)\n    result.bars          # positioned bars with individual heights\n    result.decorations   # solid shapes (wheels, windows, etc.)\n\nReturns an `ExBarcode.Shape.Result` with normalized 0.0–1.0 coordinates.\nAny renderer scales to desired size.\n\nAvailable shapes: `:rv`, `:camper`, `:city`, `:wave`, `:diamond`, `:hill`","ref":"ExBarcode.html#module-shaped-encoding-creative-barcodes"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.available_shapes/0","doc":"See  ExBarcode.Shape.available_shapes/0 .","ref":"ExBarcode.html#available_shapes/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.encode/1","doc":"See  ExBarcode.Code128.encode/1 .","ref":"ExBarcode.html#encode/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.encode!/1","doc":"See  ExBarcode.Code128.encode!/1 .","ref":"ExBarcode.html#encode!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.encode_shaped/2","doc":"See  ExBarcode.Shape.encode/2 .","ref":"ExBarcode.html#encode_shaped/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.encode_shaped!/2","doc":"See  ExBarcode.Shape.encode!/2 .","ref":"ExBarcode.html#encode_shaped!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.total_modules/1","doc":"See  ExBarcode.Code128.total_modules/1 .","ref":"ExBarcode.html#total_modules/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExBarcode.Code128","doc":"Code 128 barcode encoder.\n\nEncodes a string into a list of bar widths suitable for rendering.\nSupports Code 128B (full ASCII) with automatic Code C optimization\nfor runs of digit pairs.","ref":"ExBarcode.Code128.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Reference - ExBarcode.Code128","doc":"Code 128 uses three character sets (A, B, C). This implementation\nprimarily uses Code B (covers ASCII 32–127) with automatic switching\nto Code C for efficient encoding of digit pairs.","ref":"ExBarcode.Code128.html#module-reference"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.Code128.encode/1","doc":"Encode a string into Code 128 bar pattern.\n\nReturns `{:ok, bars}` where `bars` is a flat list of integers\nrepresenting alternating bar and space widths (starting with a bar).\n\nReturns `{:error, reason}` if the input contains unsupported characters.","ref":"ExBarcode.Code128.html#encode/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.Code128.encode!/1","doc":"Same as `encode/1` but raises on error.","ref":"ExBarcode.Code128.html#encode!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.Code128.total_modules/1","doc":"Calculate the total width in modules (unit bar widths) for a given text.","ref":"ExBarcode.Code128.html#total_modules/1"},{"type":"module","title":"ExBarcode.Shape","doc":"Shape barcode engine — transforms a standard Code 128 barcode into a\nshaped barcode with two rendering styles:","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Styles - ExBarcode.Shape","doc":"### `:silhouette` (animals, objects)\nSolid filled silhouette (head, ears, tail, legs) with barcode bars placed\ninside a rectangular region within the body. Like a cookie-cutter: the\nanimal is solid, the barcode is the \"window\" inside it.\n\n### `:contour` (geometric, abstract)\nBars with variable heights following a top/bottom contour, with optional\ndecorations (circles, polygons, lines).","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html#module-styles"},{"type":"module","title":"Output - ExBarcode.Shape","doc":"All coordinates are **normalized** to a 0.0–1.0 bounding box so\nany renderer (PDF, SVG, Canvas) can scale to the desired size.\n\n    %ExBarcode.Shape.Result{\n      style: :silhouette,\n      bars: [%{x: 0.20, y: 0.10, w: 0.005, h: 0.50}, ...],\n      silhouette: [[{0.05, 0.40}, {0.10, 0.55}, ...]],\n      barcode_region: {0.20, 0.08, 0.60, 0.52},\n      cutouts: [{:circle_bg, {0.12, 0.52, 0.02}}],\n      decorations: [{:circle, {0.11, 0.52, 0.006}}],\n      text: \"BUNNY\",\n      aspect_ratio: 1.8\n    }","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html#module-output"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.Shape.available_shapes/0","doc":"List all available predefined shapes.","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html#available_shapes/0"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.Shape.encode/2","doc":"Encode text as a shaped barcode.","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html#encode/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - ExBarcode.Shape.encode/2","doc":"- `:shape` — predefined shape atom (see `available_shapes/0`)\n  - `:contour_top` — custom top contour `[{x_pct, y_pct}, ...]`\n  - `:contour_bottom` — custom bottom contour\n  - `:quiet_zone` — modules of padding per side (default `2`)\n  - `:bar_min` — minimum bar height fraction (default `0.0`)","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html#encode/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"ExBarcode.Shape.encode!/2","doc":"Same as `encode/2` but raises on error.","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.html#encode!/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExBarcode.Shape.Result","doc":"Shaped barcode result — bars + shape data in normalized coords.","ref":"ExBarcode.Shape.Result.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"ExBarcode","doc":"# ExBarcode\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/ex_barcode.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_barcode)\n[![Docs](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-hexdocs-blue)](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_barcode)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/l/ex_barcode.svg)](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md)\n\nPure Elixir barcode encoding — Code 128 (full ASCII). No external\ndependencies. Returns bar patterns as lists of module widths suitable for\nany renderer (PDF, SVG, Canvas, etc.).\n\nPart of the [ExPDF](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf) umbrella.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - ExBarcode","doc":"```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_barcode, \"~> 0.1\"}\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usage - ExBarcode","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#usage"},{"type":"extras","title":"Standard encoding - ExBarcode","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, bars} = ExBarcode.encode(\"Hello-123\")\n# Returns alternating bar/space module widths\n```","ref":"readme.html#standard-encoding"},{"type":"extras","title":"Shaped encoding (creative barcodes) - ExBarcode","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, result} = ExBarcode.encode_shaped(\"DEMOCAMP\", shape: :rv)\nresult.bars          # positioned bars with individual heights\nresult.decorations   # solid shapes (wheels, windows, etc.)\n```\n\nReturns an `ExBarcode.Shape.Result` with normalized 0.0–1.0 coordinates.\nAny renderer scales to desired size.\n\nAvailable shapes: `:rv`, `:camper`, `:city`, `:wave`, `:diamond`, `:hill`","ref":"readme.html#shaped-encoding-creative-barcodes"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - ExBarcode","doc":"MIT. See [LICENSE.md](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md).","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.2"}}